### HYMN CXXIX

#### A charm for success and happiness

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0612901">1</span></span>With fortune
of the Sisu tree—with Indra as my friend to aid  
  I give myself a happy fate. Fly and begone, Malignities!  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0612902">2</span></span>That
splendour and felicity wherewith thou hast excelled the  
   trees  
  Give me therewith a happy fate. Fly and begone, Malignities  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0612903">3</span></span>Blind
fortune, with reverted leaves that is deposited in trees—  
  Give me therewith a happy fate. Fly and begone, Malignities.

